Title: Renormalization Group in Zero-Point Energy Calculations
Authors: Igor O. Cherednikov
Comments: Talk at the conference Renormalization Group 2002 (March 10-16, High
  Tatras, Slovakia). 4 pages, LaTeX
Journal-ref: Acta Phys.Slov. 52 (2002) 221-225
\\
  The simple consequences of the renormalization group invariance in
calculations of the ground state energy for models of confined quantum fields
are discussed. The case of (1+1)D MIT quark bag model is considered in detail.
